example.statement:
					Find the derivative of the following functions.


 F(y) = \lrpar{\dfrac{1}{y^2}-\dfrac{3}{y^4}}(y+5y^3)



 J(v) = (v^3-2v)(v^{-4}+v^{-2})



 f(x) = \dfrac{1+2x}{3-4x}



 Y(t)=\dfrac{1}{t^3+2t^2-1}



 h(u) = \dfrac{(u+2)^2}{1-u}



 f(t) = \dfrac{\sqrt[3]{t}}{t-3}

Suppose that f(4) = 2, g(4) = 5, f'(4) = 6, and g'(4) = -3.  Find h'(4) if:



		h(x) = 3f(x) + 8g(x)




		h(x) = f(x)g(x)




		h(x) = \dfrac{f(x)}{g(x)}




		h(x) = \dfrac{g(x)}{f(x) + g(x)}

If f is a differentiable function, find an expression for the derivative of each of the following:



		y = x^3f(x)




		y = \dfrac{f(x)}{x}




		y = \dfrac{x^2}{f(x)}




		y = \dfrac{1 + xf(x)}{\sqrt{x}}
